gomodel:SYNGO_9  a        owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Immunogold labeling shows localisation close to the presynaptic plasmamembrane and in the cytosol. Since it is a channel its expected location is in the membrane.\n\n5/12/2016 Pim:\n- integral component in the annotation is derived from TM-domains in the annotated protein.\n- Literal excerpt: \"Gold particles (5 nm in diameter) are localized in the presynaptic terminal close to the presynaptic plasma membrane (arrowhead) and within the cytoplasm of the PF synapse (arrow)\" [5/12/2016 Pim]\n- Fig 3b shows presynaptic localization in the **mouse** by using a biochemical approach. This annotation was omitted for now.. Experimental description: Results: \"In immunoelectron microscopy images on **rat** cerebellum using a well-characterized anti-K V 10.1 antibody (mAb62; Hemmerlein et al. 2006; Martin et al. 2008; G ' omez-Varela et al. 2010) K V 10.1 was preferentially localized to the synapses of the parallel fibres onto the Purkinje cell spines (Fig. 3 A ).\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_9" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

